1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:02,127
[Mouse squeaks]

2
00:00:02,127 --> 00:00:03,670
[Penguins chirp]

3
00:00:04,755 --> 00:00:05,714
[Screeches]

4
00:00:05,756 --> 00:00:07,883
[All cheering]

5
00:00:09,927 --> 00:00:10,928
[Screeches]

6
00:00:10,928 --> 00:00:12,429
[Quacks]

7
00:00:13,055 --> 00:00:14,181
s "Adventure Time" &

8
00:00:14,181 --> 00:00:15,641
s Come on, grab your friends 7

9
00:00:15,682 --> 00:00:18,268
J We're going to
very distant lands J

10
00:00:18,352 --> 00:00:20,604
J With Jake the dog
and Finn the human &

11
00:00:20,646 --> 00:00:22,147
J The fun will never end J

12
00:00:22,231 --> 00:00:24,024
J It's "Adventure Time" &

13
00:00:36,828 --> 00:00:40,707
Hmm. Let's see what else
the cards say.

14
00:00:47,464 --> 00:00:49,591
This card means you're a man.

15
00:00:49,591 --> 00:00:50,801
Okay.

16
00:00:50,842 --> 00:00:52,844
[Laughs]
No, I'm kidding.

17
00:00:52,970 --> 00:00:54,054
It means you're nice.

18
00:00:54,596 --> 00:00:56,723
I'm learning truth about myself.

19
00:00:56,848 --> 00:00:58,433
[Laughs]

20
00:00:58,475 --> 00:01:01,436
Hey, Dad, what if
I called you "Papa"?

21
00:01:01,478 --> 00:01:02,938
"I love the sea, Papa!"

22
00:01:04,189 --> 00:01:05,691
How are your card fingers
feeling?

23
00:01:05,774 --> 00:01:07,693
That's a weird thing
to say, Papa.

24
00:01:08,318 --> 00:01:10,946
Have you seen cards
like...this?!

25
00:01:12,406 --> 00:01:13,574
What?

26
00:01:13,657 --> 00:01:15,826
No! Not today!

27
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:18,579
- No Card Wars!
-[Splash]

28
00:01:19,830 --> 00:01:21,582
She sunk like a stone!

29
00:01:21,665 --> 00:01:22,583
[Groans]

30
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:27,212
Ah, there's no time to go back!

31
00:01:27,296 --> 00:01:28,839
The tourney starts in an hour!

32
00:01:28,922 --> 00:01:30,424
BMO is always fine.

33
00:01:30,465 --> 00:01:31,967
I don't understand.

34
00:01:33,677 --> 00:01:37,347
Card Wars, the great
and venerable game of old.

35
00:01:37,431 --> 00:01:40,809
It is the king and queen
of tabletop games.

36
00:01:41,435 --> 00:01:44,855
It combines the mechanics
of simulated combat,

37
00:01:44,855 --> 00:01:46,356
hand management,

38
00:01:46,356 --> 00:01:48,066
commodity speculation,

39
00:01:48,108 --> 00:01:49,359
Worker placement,

40
00:01:49,359 --> 00:01:50,861
blind auctioning,

41
00:01:50,861 --> 00:01:53,113
and set collection.

42
00:01:53,739 --> 00:01:56,325
Battle happens
in one of four combat lanes,

43
00:01:56,366 --> 00:02:00,495
each deriving its power from one
of the 16 themed elements --

44
00:02:00,621 --> 00:02:03,498
corn, wheat, blue, crystals,

45
00:02:03,498 --> 00:02:08,670
acumen, torpor, frozen lakes,
lizard holes, learning...

46
00:02:09,171 --> 00:02:11,882
[Waves rumbling]

47
00:02:28,315 --> 00:02:29,650
[Yawns loudly]

48
00:02:29,691 --> 00:02:31,151
That's too many rules.

49
00:02:31,193 --> 00:02:33,153
I don't do cards
to follow rules.

50
00:02:33,195 --> 00:02:35,072
But you could be so good!

51
00:02:35,155 --> 00:02:36,948
Daddy's pro-tege!

52
00:02:37,032 --> 00:02:39,451
Of course I'd be good at it,
but I'm not into it.

53
00:02:39,534 --> 00:02:42,204
Look, I lost track
of how old I am.

54
00:02:42,287 --> 00:02:44,790
Maybe I'm almost 40.
I don't know.

55
00:02:44,831 --> 00:02:47,167
I at least need
to unpack my /ast decade

56
00:02:47,209 --> 00:02:49,711
before embarking
on my next decade.

57
00:02:49,711 --> 00:02:51,963
I've got to win
and be dignified.

58
00:02:51,963 --> 00:02:55,217
20s are for regretting,
30s are for being dignified,

59
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:57,928
and 40s are older
than I ever want to be.

60
00:02:57,969 --> 00:02:59,721
Hmm.

61
00:02:59,805 --> 00:03:01,306
O...kay.

62
00:03:01,348 --> 00:03:03,600
You give me one of your...

63
00:03:03,684 --> 00:03:06,311
bones...

64
00:03:06,353 --> 00:03:10,315
and I'll play one of your games.

65
00:03:24,454 --> 00:03:26,123
-[Electricity crackles]
-[Groans]

66
00:03:35,132 --> 00:03:36,758
DOORMAN:
I activate the Barrel.

67
00:03:37,843 --> 00:03:39,636
JAKE:
I floop the Cooper.

68
00:03:39,636 --> 00:03:41,638
- Mmmwah!
- Mmmwah!

69
00:03:41,722 --> 00:03:43,140
Cute!

70
00:03:45,892 --> 00:03:50,355
Welcome, Charlie, to the 59th
Card Wars Doubles Classic!

71
00:03:50,397 --> 00:03:53,108
That's Todd and Jennings
signing in.

72
00:03:53,150 --> 00:03:55,902
And over there,
Benton and Mike R.

73
00:03:55,986 --> 00:03:58,488
Luke and Captain Majesty.

74
00:03:58,530 --> 00:04:01,158
Mr. Outrageous
and Mr. International.

75
00:04:01,241 --> 00:04:03,034
Who's that, Papa?

76
00:04:03,118 --> 00:04:06,288
That's...uh...
the reigning champs.

77
00:04:06,371 --> 00:04:07,122
Jake?

78
00:04:07,164 --> 00:04:09,416
[Waves build]

79
00:04:09,541 --> 00:04:10,542
Grand Prix.

80
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:12,753
GRAND PRIX: Man, I thought
you swore off tourney play,

81
00:04:12,794 --> 00:04:14,629
like, angrily swore it off.

82
00:04:14,671 --> 00:04:16,590
-[Moniker clears throat]
- GRAND PRIX: Oh. Uh, pardon.

83
00:04:16,631 --> 00:04:17,591
Hello, Jake.

84
00:04:17,632 --> 00:04:19,259
Is that you, Moniker?

85
00:04:19,384 --> 00:04:20,469
How are you?

86
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:22,220
- We've been just grea-
- Her?

87
00:04:22,262 --> 00:04:25,515
Oh, this is my daughter/
Card Wars partner, Charlie!

88
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:26,975
'Sup?

89
00:04:27,017 --> 00:04:28,393
That's fantastic, Jake.

90
00:04:28,393 --> 00:04:29,770
You always wanted kids.

91
00:04:29,895 --> 00:04:31,730
Well, she's a chip
off the old block, I'll bet.

92
00:04:31,772 --> 00:04:34,775
Us, we're running the local
after-school OW. program,

93
00:04:34,858 --> 00:04:36,777
just like where you and me
first met.

94
00:04:36,860 --> 00:04:39,154
Most days, we're busy running
the screen-printing shop,

95
00:04:39,154 --> 00:04:41,156
but, uh, we still make time
for the tourney,

96
00:04:41,156 --> 00:04:43,283
- just for fun, you know.
- [Waves crashing]

97
00:04:43,366 --> 00:04:45,911
Yes! We're all here
to have fun!

98
00:04:45,911 --> 00:04:48,163
Well, got to sign in.
Come, Charlie!

99
00:04:48,163 --> 00:04:49,289
Nice meeting you.

100
00:04:49,915 --> 00:04:52,167
- That's your ex, huh?
- What?

101
00:04:52,167 --> 00:04:55,003
Nothing.
You've definitely got a type.

102
00:04:55,045 --> 00:04:56,797
[Laughs]

103
00:04:57,547 --> 00:04:58,673
ANNOUNCER: Round 1!

104
00:04:58,757 --> 00:05:02,052
Jake and Charlie,
A.K.A. Team Dignified,

105
00:05:02,052 --> 00:05:04,054
Versus Reggie and Pete the punk.

106
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:06,014
- Ohhhh!
- Blah, blah, blah!

107
00:05:06,056 --> 00:05:09,309
Commence Card Wars!

108
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:15,899
I floop the Hay Barn,
and I attack with Feed Man!

109
00:05:15,941 --> 00:05:18,068
ANNOUNCER: A solid move
from the veteran Jake.

110
00:05:18,151 --> 00:05:21,404
Least Bean Ball Bomba.

111
00:05:21,446 --> 00:05:23,198
ANNOUNCER:
Bean Ball!

112
00:05:23,198 --> 00:05:24,699
Bean Ball?!

113
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:28,203
ANNOUNCER: Feed Man's
power source is gone!

114
00:05:28,286 --> 00:05:29,830
No, no, no!

115
00:05:29,913 --> 00:05:32,040
No...big deal.

116
00:05:32,082 --> 00:05:34,584
[Inhales sharply]
Your turn, sweetie.

117
00:05:34,584 --> 00:05:35,710
Okay.

118
00:05:35,794 --> 00:05:37,587
I'll play...

119
00:05:37,671 --> 00:05:38,839
this one.

120
00:05:39,798 --> 00:05:40,841
[Beep]

121
00:05:40,966 --> 00:05:42,551
[Chuckles]
"Floop."

122
00:05:42,592 --> 00:05:45,303
[Whirrrrr!]

123
00:05:45,345 --> 00:05:47,973
Granary Weeuvil,
on your first draw?!

124
00:05:48,098 --> 00:05:49,099
Unprecedented.

125
00:05:49,182 --> 00:05:53,103
And combined with a downed
Feed Man, that means...

126
00:05:53,228 --> 00:05:55,856
ANNOUNCER: He's right.
It's Infinite Haymaker!

127
00:05:55,856 --> 00:05:56,690
That's game!

128
00:05:56,731 --> 00:05:58,984
A stunning move
from the newcomer Charlie.

129
00:05:58,984 --> 00:06:00,485
She's a real pro-tege.

130
00:06:00,569 --> 00:06:01,611
We win!

131
00:06:01,695 --> 00:06:03,864
- Whoo! [Laughs]
-[Laughing]

132
00:06:03,947 --> 00:06:05,323
Yeah, I'm out.

133
00:06:05,365 --> 00:06:06,199
What?!

134
00:06:06,241 --> 00:06:08,243
One bone, one game.

135
00:06:08,326 --> 00:06:10,745
But I'm not done burying my 20s.

136
00:06:10,829 --> 00:06:12,622
Do you want more bones?
Is that it?!

137
00:06:15,250 --> 00:06:16,960
Nah.
I only need one.

138
00:06:17,002 --> 00:06:18,628
Catch ya on the flip, Papa.

139
00:06:18,712 --> 00:06:19,713
[Squish!]

140
00:06:19,754 --> 00:06:21,131
[Rattle!]

141
00:06:21,214 --> 00:06:23,091
ANNOUNCER:
Round 2 starts in five minutes.

142
00:06:28,471 --> 00:06:29,639
Still dignified.

143
00:06:29,723 --> 00:06:30,640
Psst.

144
00:06:30,724 --> 00:06:32,392
Lost your partner, huh?

145
00:06:32,517 --> 00:06:34,269
Hey, don't worry.
We won't tattle.

146
00:06:34,394 --> 00:06:35,854
[Ting!]

147
00:06:35,896 --> 00:06:39,149
I will crush you, Grand Prix.

148
00:06:39,149 --> 00:06:41,359
[Wind Whistling]

149
00:06:55,165 --> 00:06:57,000
I'm ho-o-me!

150
00:06:58,168 --> 00:06:59,794
Hey, you two been kissing?

151
00:07:02,672 --> 00:07:03,757
What-what?!

152
00:07:03,798 --> 00:07:05,175
[Creak!]

153
00:07:06,885 --> 00:07:08,637
Me hungy.

154
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:09,930
Gomp!

155
00:07:13,767 --> 00:07:16,561
All y'all keep quiet!
Charlie's flexin'!

156
00:07:17,646 --> 00:07:18,563
Let's see.

157
00:07:18,647 --> 00:07:20,899
Finally, I've got
the hair of the mother

158
00:07:20,941 --> 00:07:22,567
and a bone of the father.

159
00:07:22,651 --> 00:07:25,654
Time to do a rare turbo-boosted
personal reading.

160
00:07:25,695 --> 00:07:27,697
Self-care mega-blow.

161
00:07:29,532 --> 00:07:30,909
ANNOUNCER:
It's the semifinal round,

162
00:07:30,951 --> 00:07:33,828
and Mr. Outrageous has Jake
on the ropes.

163
00:07:33,828 --> 00:07:35,956
JAKE: [Thinking] I can still
play my Ultra Dog

164
00:07:36,081 --> 00:07:37,290
and force a draw.

165
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:38,792
And while technically
a legal move,

166
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:40,543
it's considered
a low-class maneuver

167
00:07:40,585 --> 00:07:41,795
this late in the tourney.

168
00:07:41,836 --> 00:07:42,462
[Groans]

169
00:07:42,545 --> 00:07:44,047
Jake.

170
00:07:45,215 --> 00:07:47,175
Do it!

171
00:07:48,593 --> 00:07:51,596
I play...Ultra Dog!

172
00:07:51,596 --> 00:07:53,098
ANNOUNCER:
A shocking move!

173
00:07:53,223 --> 00:07:56,851
Ultra Dog attacks the
Tilled Field with "Cold Nose"!

174
00:07:56,977 --> 00:07:59,187
Which means...cat's game!

175
00:07:59,229 --> 00:08:00,730
But by tourney rules,

176
00:08:00,855 --> 00:08:04,067
the slight point lead gives
the win to Team Dignified!

177
00:08:04,109 --> 00:08:07,737
They advance to the finals
versus Grand Prix and Moniker.

178
00:08:07,821 --> 00:08:09,447
Just a garbage, garbage win.

179
00:08:10,865 --> 00:08:12,742
[Chuckles evilly]

180
00:08:12,867 --> 00:08:14,619
[Gasps]
What am I doing?!

181
00:08:14,619 --> 00:08:16,621
[Waves rumbling]

182
00:08:21,501 --> 00:08:23,336
[Cards shuffle]

183
00:08:23,378 --> 00:08:26,256
All right.
The deck is ripe.

184
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:28,133
Let's see what the cards say.

185
00:08:34,014 --> 00:08:36,016
Dad!
Why are you here?

186
00:08:36,057 --> 00:08:37,308
This one's about mel

187
00:08:40,812 --> 00:08:42,939
[Groaning]

188
00:08:43,064 --> 00:08:46,192
That's too much sandwich!
You got to chew!

189
00:08:49,696 --> 00:08:51,281
Gah!

190
00:08:51,322 --> 00:08:53,158
Is this my 20s?

191
00:08:53,199 --> 00:08:54,409
Dad was right.

192
00:08:54,451 --> 00:08:57,579
I've got to fix
these "faults of youth."

193
00:09:03,460 --> 00:09:04,836
My 30s?

194
00:09:04,961 --> 00:09:06,546
I look lost.

195
00:09:08,298 --> 00:09:09,841
My 40s.

196
00:09:09,966 --> 00:09:11,468
I'm afraid.

197
00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:13,845
Also, I'm naming you "Gibbon."

198
00:09:15,597 --> 00:09:17,599
My 50s.

199
00:09:17,724 --> 00:09:19,350
Midlife crisis.

200
00:09:19,350 --> 00:09:20,852
Good luck, Gibbon!

201
00:09:22,812 --> 00:09:24,314
My 60s.

202
00:09:24,355 --> 00:09:27,067
I'm unfamiliar
with my changing body.

203
00:09:28,860 --> 00:09:30,361
My 70s.

204
00:09:30,445 --> 00:09:32,614
I begin
to lose people around me.

205
00:09:34,616 --> 00:09:36,117
My 80s.

206
00:09:36,201 --> 00:09:38,119
I'm afraid again.

207
00:09:39,621 --> 00:09:41,122
My 90s.

208
00:09:41,247 --> 00:09:43,458
I'm content and wise!

209
00:09:48,254 --> 00:09:49,464
Yeah!

210
00:09:49,506 --> 00:09:50,882
Wrinkles!

211
00:09:50,882 --> 00:09:52,383
Oh, no!

212
00:09:52,383 --> 00:09:55,011
I've been a total wand
to my dad!

213
00:09:55,095 --> 00:09:56,763
I've got to go help him!

214
00:09:56,888 --> 00:09:59,390
Come on, Jakey.
pull it together.

215
00:09:59,390 --> 00:10:01,976
Blah! Win!
Win at all costs!

216
00:10:02,018 --> 00:10:03,394
No! I bury you!

217
00:10:03,478 --> 00:10:04,771
Feel your 20s!

218
00:10:04,771 --> 00:10:06,147
No, no, no!

219
00:10:06,231 --> 00:10:07,398
CHARLIE: Be cool.

220
00:10:08,149 --> 00:10:09,150
Mom?

221
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:11,152
No, Papa.
It's your 90-year-old daughter.

222
00:10:12,153 --> 00:10:13,738
You flake!

223
00:10:13,780 --> 00:10:15,281
Be content.

224
00:10:15,281 --> 00:10:17,617
[Screams]

225
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:18,910
Whoa!

226
00:10:19,035 --> 00:10:21,371
Whoo! Whoo!

227
00:10:21,371 --> 00:10:22,872
- Whoop! Whoop!
- Whoop! Whoop!

228
00:10:22,914 --> 00:10:24,541
[Both Whooping]

229
00:10:24,624 --> 00:10:25,542
Ka-pow!

230
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:26,543
- Whoop!
- Yeah!

231
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:27,669
- Whoop!
- What-what?!

232
00:10:27,752 --> 00:10:29,170
Dignified!

233
00:10:46,771 --> 00:10:47,939
Yeah!

234
00:10:48,022 --> 00:10:51,901
Winners -- Grand Prix
and Moniker Des Louise.

235
00:10:51,943 --> 00:10:54,195
[Waves rumbling]

236
00:10:58,575 --> 00:10:59,826
[Rumbling fades]

237
00:10:59,909 --> 00:11:02,287
Good game, Grand Prix, Moniker.

238
00:11:11,713 --> 00:11:13,798
[Chuckles]
Okay.

239
00:11:15,967 --> 00:11:20,054
s Come along with me J

240
00:11:20,096 --> 00:11:24,350
J And the butterflies and bees &

241
00:11:27,228 --> 00:11:29,564
This party is so crazy!

